CAPE TOWN - First built for military purposes, remotely controlled drones now have several commercial uses, and drone enthusiasts have turned their love of flying them into a sport.Since its rapid progression, South Africa has now been introduced to the competitive aspect of their hobby.Much like a Formula One driver, pilots race each other on various circuits, using a drone that they have built to handle the obstacles.Apart from that, they are also tested on the functionality of the drone in the freestyle segment.eNCA s sports reporter Amy Samuels has more on the story in the video gallery above. eNCA